="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Wong</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">YC</span></span>, Wang LJ, Chen CJ. MRI of an isolated traumatic perforation of the gallbladder. <em>J Comput Assist Tomogr</em>2000; 24: 657–658.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1097/00004728-200007000-00028">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/10966206/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=J+Comput+Assist+Tomogr&amp;publication_year=2000&amp;pages=657&amp;doi=10.1097%2F00004728-200007000-00028&amp;pmid=10966206">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div></section></div><div class="core-collateral" role="dialog" aria-modal="true"><div id="core-collateral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2></header><section id="tab-information" role="tabpanel"><h3>Information</h3><section class="core-self-citation"><h4>Published In</h4><div class="core-journal-presentation">



        
        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/28/6" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2008.28.issue-6/asset/14a1685b-fc14-1685-7fc1-a1685b7fc14a/radiographics.2008.28.issue-6.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">28</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">6</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Oct 1 2008</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1591</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1602</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18936023/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">18936023</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2008.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Oct 1 2008</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.286085524">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=AAST+%3D+American+Association+for+the+Surgery+of+Trauma&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">AAST = American Association for the Surgery of Trauma</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ERCP+%3D+endoscopic+retrograde+cholangiopancreatography&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ERCP = endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MRCP+%3D+MR+cholangiopancreatography&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MRCP = MR cholangiopancreatography</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The current role of multidetector CT in diagnosis of pancreatic and duodenal injuries is reviewed, appropriate multidetector CT protocols are described, multidetector CT–based classifications of organ injuries for trauma scoring are presented, and the roles of MR cholangiopancreatography and endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography are discussed.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Ulrich</span> <span property="familyName">Linsenmaier</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD, PhD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Clinical Radiology, Ludwig-Maximilians-University Munich, Nussbaumstrasse 20, D-80336 Munich, Germany. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received April 3, 2008; revision requested June 17 and received July 1; accepted July 9. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Linsenmaier/Ulrich" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Stefan</span> <span property="familyName">Wirth</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Clinical Radiology, Ludwig-Maximilians-University Munich, Nussbaumstrasse 20, D-80336 Munich, Germany. Presented as an education exhibit at the 2007 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received April 